The article announces the nomination of Jerome M. Adams as the Medical Director in the Regular Corps of the Public Health Service and the potential appointment as Surgeon General of the Public Health Service for a four-year term. Adams is currently the Indiana State Health Commissioner and has previously worked as a Staff Anesthesiologist and Assistant Professor of Anesthesia at the Indiana University School of Medicine. He has a BS in Biochemistry and a BA in Biopsychology from the University of Maryland Baltimore County, a Masters in Public Health from the University of California at Berkeley, and an MD from the Indiana University School of Medicine. Adams has received several awards, including the Indiana Center for Leadership Development Achievement Award, the Sagamore of the Wabash Award (highest civilian honor from the State of Indiana), the Indiana Rural Health Association Health Policy Advocate Award, the Indiana University Early Career Achievement Award, and the Indiana University Teaching Award.